	<ul id="p2">
		<li>Use familiar HTML5 technologies to build native-looking apps.</li>
		<li>Works across multiple platforms.</li>
		<li>Provides consistent look and feel for mobile applications.</li></ul>

	<h3>Disadvantages ?<span id="down3"><i class="fas fa-sort-down fa-1x"></i></span></h3>
	<ul id="p3"><li>Relies on the platform's browser,which may or may not support all of the library's features.</li>
                <li>Doesn't provide native access to some platform features.</li>
                <li>Performance is slower than true native code.</li></ul>
